caption: 104 is a breath of fresh air! An exceptional cultural hub where arts and talents intertwine seamlessly - from theater to dance, music to visual arts.  It's a melting pot of diverse populations and instruments, a true testament to Paris's vibrancy. The future undoubtedly unfolds here. I've encountered few places worldwide as inspiring.

Amazing space for art exhibitions and dance. The entrance there is free (for training or dancing or just taking a look) but expositions are not free so better check online to get your tickets in advance so can do both :)

An amazing space of art and dance. You can go there for free just to train in dancing, or to visit the amazing expositions - not for free - or to drink something - not for free either. Oh there's also a book library. By the way, this place made history and requalified the area, even if it's still a mess.

Went here for the AOP cheese festival in April - it was so good! Amazing cheeses, great service, the only thing I would say is the queues at the bar were too busy so could have done with more bars / bar staff!
Best spot to go to if you feel like dancing (trying skills etc) as there is a lot of good dancers around

An amazing cultural space in Paris! The venue is huge! You can find arts, expos, a restaurant, second hand shops for the good cause, people rehearsing for their art performance, people dancing!! The vibe it there is really gorgeous. It‚Äôs definitely worth a visit. Went for the numeric art expo, only slight drawback is that there‚Äôs several rooms and you have to queue for each room.
Cool and laid-back vibe with characterful and uncommercial cafes, dance space and bookshops.  A fascinating use of the old Paris abattoir

Places like this should be in all cities. Where else should all these people go and rehearse? We spent about an hour exploring this phantastic location and then had a nice coffee in the "hidden place".
Great place to skate and juggle had some cool arty things to do as well such a fun space and good vibe

This is a free space for singers, dancers, artists and everyone with a passion for art. Mostly young people, but certainly no age limit. It's a bit like Darwin Ecosystem in Bordeaux or 798 Art Zone in Beijing, but more active, more energetic and more interactive. It's somewhere that you can get really close to the artists.
A nice place for practicing dance lessons. Also there are some activities during the season which you can attend (have a look at their website first).

Incredible Arts and Culture space in Paris, You can find coffee and a restaurant, while enjoying of dance rehearsals, expositions, vintage clothing and music. Is a very special place that every art lover should visit.

Awesome venue, despite the long queue to get in. I should have grabbed a deck chair before the gig (OPN) started, as the area at the back and slightly above the main stage area seemed like the perfect spot to sit and enjoy the show. Despite the vape haze, visibility was good and the only thing I really missed was a decent laser show to cut through the clouds belched out by the smoke machine. Special props for ginger beer availability at the caf√© bar.
Cool place Caught cheese d√©gustation there
Live, full of people! Amazing cultural space hosting incredible plays.
Lovely place dedicated to exhibitions √©vent and contemporary arts üëç ‚Ä¶
It's an amazing free space to hang out and express yourself.

Can't say enough about how great this place is. Full of people in creative fields (painting, dancing, theatre, sculpture, juggling, acrobatics, roller-skating etc). One of these wonderful spaces that bring people together. A great program of activities all year around.
Saw a wonderful dance performance. The performers were quite flexible, although I‚Äôm not sure exactly what the story was trying to saw. It was about an hour long.
Arrived too early but the place was buzzing. Will have to return.
Amazing place, big area for do all and i love the old photo machine.

I love this place! I don‚Äôt even know how to describe it. The creative energy of people who have gathered to rehearse is incredible. Every performance is spectacular that I have seen in the theatre. A real gem and the opposite of a tourist trap in every way.
I was totally impressed by the whole location. The spaces, the architecture, inside and outside, just great.
In district 19. I like this venue. Open and bright.

Very nice cultural place to practice art, you'll find also restaurants, shops, you can spend some time there. No change! Always a nice place to spend an afternoon looking at dancers training, or exhibitions, just read free access books, buy cultural products, enjoy a meal or drink..
Interesting cultural place to visit - lots of young people dancing, art exhibits and installations, places to eat, and a few shops as well.
I love it here because it has a contemporary and urban vibe. It is a really nice place for young people to practice contemporary arts.
Interesting place with the good atmosphere. If you are around definitely visit this place!

Was a very nice venue for the concert I attended. Small and cozy, but with wonderful sound and comfortable seats. It was easy to find and the staff were extremely kind upon entering, and made sure you were where you needed to be. I would most definitely come here for another concert anytime!
Really cute place, full of kids doing their thing

The vibes of this place is great. Its Open to all and inclusive. You will find many performers practicing in the big hall and they also have a place for children.  And there are some art exhibitions and installations from time to time. And ball pop (great music and lot of dancing) once each month i suppose.
Nice to see people are dancing, performing freely.  A place you may come with your children‚Ä¶there is a bar&restaurant also. You may spend time in clothing store!

Such a beautiful place, events and exhibitions take place here and right in the centre is a place where artists and acrobats come to practise their arts. The seating area around allows passers by to sit back and enjoy the show. Depending on the artists sometimes you can walk up to them to chat and if they're nice enough they'll even give you a little free lesson.
Very interesting not touristic place, kind of a public space for people who like dancing!

Very handsome space. Used to be a warehouse/factory for making coffins and gravestones. It's been carefully renovated and is a big cultural center with dance, concerts, and expos. Also there's an Emmaus shop inside and a cafe. Definitely worth stopping by foe a look if you're in the area
One of the most amazing places we visited in Paris. Super friendly staff and great atmosphere in the building. You can se extraordinary dancing here.

An incredible community space; a buzzing huge indoor open space for dance, and all kinds of movement activities; a small market, a couple of reasonable cafe's, an awesome parent/baby play space (although limited entrance, so you have to wait sometimes). Sometimes installations too.

Great space to take the entire family or wander around the 2  restaurants bookshop thrift shop kids area smaller galleries.  Many creative practising as well from actors dancers to circus performers.  Also a great concert space.
